miRBase precursor idClicking this field will display a pdf of the structure and read signature of the miRNA. total read countthis is the sum of read counts for the 5p and 3p sequences. 5p read countsthis is the number of reads that map to the miRNA hairpin and are contained in the sequence covered by the 5p sequence, including 2 nts upstream and 5 nts downstream. In parenthesis are normalized read counts shown. 3p read countsthis is the number of reads that map to the miRNA hairpin and are contained in the sequence covered by the 3p sequence, including 2 nts upstream and 5 nts downstream. In parenthesis are normalized read counts shown. remaining readsthis is the number of reads that did not map to any of the 5p or 3p sequences UCSC browserif a species name was input to miRDeep2, then clicking this field will initiate a UCSC blat search of the miRNA precursor sequence against the reference genome. NCBI blastnclicking this field will initiate a NCBI blastn search of the miRNA precursor sequence against the nr/nt database (non-redundant collection of all NCBI nucleotide sequences). miRBase 5p sequence(s)this is/are the 5p miRNA sequence(s) input to quantifier.pl. miRBase 3p sequence(s)this is/are the 3p miRNA sequence(s) input to quantifier.pl. miRBase precursor sequencethis is the precursor miRNA sequence input to quantifier.pl.
